  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contract obligations for NAICS 339112 (Surgical and Medical Instrument Manufacturing) totaled $722M in FY2026 to date. There were 7,610 awards with an average award size of $94.9K, and obligations were down 55.2% year over year. Recent fiscal-year history shows prior obligations of $2.3B in FY21, $1.1B in FY22, $1.5B in FY23, $2B in FY24, and $1.6B in FY25. The Department of Veterans Affairs accounted for the bulk of current-year obligations with $631M, followed by the Department of Defense at $39.2M and the Department of Health and Human Services at $35.4M. The largest contractors by obligations in FY2026 to date are SDV OFFICE SYSTEMS LLC at $131M, FIRST NATION GROUP LLC at $86.6M, and OLYMPUS AMERICA INC at $74.1M. Other notable vendors include MEDICAL PLACE INC at $65M and SCRIPTPRO USA INC at $28.5M. Current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date) and reflect the mix of agency demand and vendor awards captured so far.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How did FY2026 obligations compare to prior years?",
        "body": "Obligations in FY2026 to date were $722M, down 55.2% year over year. By comparison, obligations were $1.6B in FY25, $2B in FY24, $1.5B in FY23, $1.1B in FY22, and $2.3B in FY21. The current total is a partial fiscal-year figure and reflects fewer or smaller awards to date relative to the prior year. Average award size in FY2026 to date was $94.9K across 7,610 awards."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who are the largest buyers and contractors in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "The Department of Veterans Affairs was the largest buyer at $631M, far exceeding the next agencies: the Department of Defense at $39.2M and the Department of Health and Human Services at $35.4M. The largest contractors by obligations were SDV OFFICE SYSTEMS LLC at $131M, FIRST NATION GROUP LLC at $86.6M, and OLYMPUS AMERICA INC at $74.1M. Other significant vendors include MEDICAL PLACE INC at $65M and SCRIPTPRO USA INC at $28.5M."
      }
    ]
